PRIMARY SYSTEM COMPONENTS


4   Screw Compressor Packages
1   Evaporative Condenser
1   High-Pressure / Thermosiphon Receiver
1   High Temperature Recirculator with two ammonia pumps
1   Low Temperature Recirculator with two ammonia pumps
2   Oil Pots (one at each recirculator)
5   Evaporator Coil Units (10°F Shipping Dock)
4   Evaporator Coil Units (-20°F Freezer)
1   Auto Purger
1   Ammonia Diffusion Tank (18,000 gal. capacity)

Additional system components include:

?   Interconnecting piping; and
?   Control valves

Safety systems include:

?   Pressure relief valves on all pressure vessels;
?   Compressor safety cutouts and control panels to shut down the compressor operation if safe operating conditions are exceeded;
?   Liquid level float switches;
?   High level vessel alarms;
?   Ventilation system for continuous and emergency ventilation;
?   Emergency Control Station with emergency ventilation fan switch and emergency shutdown switch;
?   Ammonia vapor detection and alarm system for response to elevated levels of ammonia vapor.  Detection will trigger the emergency ventilation system, emergency shutdown, and audible/visual alarms at preset levels;
?   Spring-loaded, self-closing oil drain valves;
?   Manual stop valves;
?   Manual and solenoid-controlled ¿King Valve¿ to stop liquid refrigerant flow from the high-pressure receiver to other components in the system;
?   Physical barriers to protect equipment/piping from collisions (e.g. bollards);
?   Fire extinguishers; and
?   Emergency showers and eyewash stations
There is an oil pot at each recirculator and each oil pot vessel is equipped with a self-closing spring-loaded drain valve for safety.  All pressure vessels in the system have dual safety relief valves (SRV's) to protect the respective vessel against overpressure conditions.  All SRV's relieve to an ammonia diffusion tank via a common discharge piping system.  An auto purger removes non-condensibles and air as required to maintain
